 Furthermore, the complex nature of indirect effects often involves multiple
 rounds of economic activity and feedback loops that are challenging to
 quantify 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "hallegatte-2015-indir-cost"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In addition to these challenges, obtaining precise data on economic production
 for short-term analysis, below the yearly scale, can be arduous.
 Such data are often not readily available or may be subject to significant
 measurement error.
 Thus, there is an urgent need to enhance our understanding of the intricate
 economic effects of disasters and their impacts on supply chains, particularly
 within the context of climate change 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "dasaklis-2013-suppl-chain"
literal "false"

