 For instance, if the model is set to rebuild 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

too fast
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 (e.g.
 3 months), indirect impacts seem extremely large (higher than 500% of the
 initial direct damages).
 This result supports the importance of careful ressources allocation after
 a disaster in order to avoid supply chains struggle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The use of different MRIOTs showed important variation in results (when
 considering a rebuilding demand).
 Using EXIOBASE 3 leads to indirect impacts lower in average than EUREGIO
 and EORA26.
 EUREGIO and EORA26 also show more variability in the results, tied with
 the presence of important negative outcomes.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Finally, changes in parameters values also largely have more influence 
